# Daniel OS Dashboard

Command-center Next.js app: sales, meetings, content, research, memory (Echo), agents, runs, approvals, schedules, alerts, integrations.

## Stack

- Next.js App Router (16+), React 19, Tailwind 4
- Prisma 7 + Postgres (`DATABASE_URL`); client generated to `src/generated/prisma` (run `npm run db:generate`)
- BullMQ + Redis (`REDIS_URL`) for queues (workers not fully wired in all paths)
- Clerk may be present; follow existing auth patterns in the repo

## Key paths

| Area | Location |
|------|----------|
| Agent definitions (canonical registry) | `src/lib/agents.ts` — `AGENT_DEFINITIONS`; seed syncs from here |
| DB access | `src/lib/db.ts` — `db` Prisma client |
| Dashboard shell | `src/app/(dashboard)/layout.tsx`, `src/components/sidebar.tsx` |
| API routes | `src/app/api/**/route.ts` |
| Schema | `prisma/schema.prisma` |

## Local port

- Default **3040** (`npm run dev` / `npm run start` use `${PORT:-3040}`). Override: `PORT=3005 npm run dev`.

## Conventions

- Prefer server components for data pages unless client interactivity is required.
- New API routes: validate body with Zod where inputs vary; return `Response.json` with appropriate status codes.
- After schema changes: `npm run db:generate` and migrate/push as documented in README.

## Next.js version note

This project may use Next APIs that differ from older training cutoffs. Prefer reading `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` or official Next docs when unsure.
